Reference: Sony Computer Entertainment PS3 SDK
----------------------------------------------
The official Sony PS3 SDK is owned by Sony Interactive Entertainment and is
covered by a separate SCE Developer License Agreement. In this project it is
used privately and exclusively as a reference (coverage oracle) for API
names, function signatures, constants, and NID values. No Sony SDK code,
headers, or binaries are copied, redistributed, or included in this repository
or its build artifacts. The reference/sony-sdk/ path is excluded from version
control via .gitignore at the repository root.

NVIDIA NV_fragment_program reference
------------------------------------
Fragment shader assembler (Phase 3) is a clean-room implementation based on
publicly documented NVIDIA NV_fragment_program OpenGL extensions and the
Nouveau project's reverse-engineered Mesa drivers. No NVIDIA proprietary
source code is used.

IBM Cell Broadband Engine intrinsics and manuals
------------------------------------------------
SPU intrinsic names, ABI, and instruction encodings are based on the public
IBM Cell Broadband Engine Architecture specification and the Sony/Toshiba/IBM
SPU C/C++ Language Extensions Specification. These are publicly published
documents; no proprietary IBM source is used.

PSDevWiki
---------
Community-maintained PS3 documentation at https://www.psdevwiki.com provided
the NID/FNID algorithm and LV2 syscall numbering referenced by this project's
tooling.

